  "text": "surfaces in multiple ways [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] We do not have any reason to believe that our [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] abelian surface fibered threefold is also an elliptic K3 fibration, nevertheless this a logical possibility. On the other hand, there seems be a folk theorem that abelian surface fibered Calabi-Yau manifolds cannot be realized as toric hypersurfaces [37] , so we deem this possibility unlikely.",
